A 31-YEAR-OLD bank employee was recently jailed to life in India for the murder of a magosha, whom he regularly visited. Hindustan Times reported that the man found out that the magosha was in a relationship with another man, which made him jealous. Mumbai City Civil & Sessions Court heard that the deceased woman was in a relationship with another man, of which convict Kumaran Konar did not like. READ: MY 4-5 built mum a house It is reported that on 31 March 2015, the deceased was standing near Alexandra Theatre at around 9.15pm when Konar approached her from behind. “He held her hands and slit her throat, and then fled from the spot. The woman was rushed to hospital, but was declared dead,” the article read. A case of murder was registered, and the man was arrested the following day. Public prosecutor Ratnavali Patil examined 12 witnesses and two eyewitnesses, who were around when the incident occurred. Handing down the judgment, it was argued that Konar often fought with her over her relationship with the other man, and the judge gave him a life sentence.